{
  "doc_id": "16133",
  "text": "Several LQTS patients have sudden pauses in sinus rhythm exceeding 1.2 seconds that are not related to sinus arrhythmia [CITATION_1] and may contribute to the initiation of arrhythmias in LQTS patients. Their occurrence in LQT3 patients represents an important warning signal, which requires reinforcing safety measures.",
